-- FTSE 100 Index Declines; Shire Shares Lead Benchmark Lower After Downgrade
-- Adam Haigh
-- 2010-07-30T07:32:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/ftse-100-index-declines-shire-shares-lead-benchmark-lower-after-downgrade.html

          
          
             U.K. stocks declined, with the
benchmark FTSE 100 Index dropping 0.4 percent to 5,291.76 as of
8:31 a.m. in London.  
 Shire Plc retreated 4.2 percent to 1,428 pence.  
          
          


  


        